The paper proposes a MIMO-assisted channel-based authentication scheme for wireless networks, which involves the use of multiple antennas to provide extra dimensions of channel estimation data for detecting spoofing attacks. This topic is closely related to the field of computer security (cs.CR), as well as information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), multimedia systems (cs.MM), and systems and control (cs.SY).
